    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-12-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-12-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="684"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d684">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">871.631/10</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 7, 1928</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received December 27.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 50</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit a copy in
                    translation of an article which appeared in the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Dreptatea</hi>,<note n="13" xml:id="d684fn13">Not printed.</note> now the
                    government organ,<note n="14" xml:id="d684fn14">A new ministry in Rumania was
                        formed Nov. 10, 1928, under Juliu Maniu, leader of the Nationalist-Peasant
                        Party.</note> reporting an interview accorded by the Minister of Industry to
                    a delegation representing local oil interests. The main point of interest is the
                    repetition of the promise given by the Government to repeal the objectionable
                    features of the mining law. Mr. Madgearu declared that the revision of this law
                    is now in course of preparation and will be drawn up as a bill to be submitted
                    to parliament.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles S. Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
